I live right down the street and have been to Switch many times. I've always had a great experience. The servers and hosts are very kind. I usually get the Breakfast Galette, but everything else that I've tried on the menu is delicious.   What I like about this restaurant is that it seems to have a great training process. I'm an indecisive person. So when it comes to choosing an entree, nothing is more frustrating when the server can't tell me how it tastes or if he/she likes it. I've never had that issue at Switch. Anything I ask about, they can tell me what it's like, to help me make my decision.

